**Direct application** of Tertiary's
`MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain.smul_of_eq_conjAct`
(`PeterssonLevelN.lean`:428), instantiated at `G_outer := GL(2, в„қ)вҒә`,
with the conjugate identification supplied by `rfl` (the output
subgroup is *defined* as that conjugate).

**Use site (DS Prop. 5.5.2(b)).**  Specialized at
`HвӮҒ := (О“_p(Оұ)).map ModularGroup.coeHom` (the GL(2, в„қ)вҒә lift of the
Hecke conjugate intersection group `Gamma_p_Оұ`), this discharges the
FD-shift content of the per-Оұ residual reduction inside the
`DSDoubleCosetTileBridge` proof: the FD `Оұ' вҖў s` together with the
conjugate-subgroup identification feeds the Petersson-integral
change-of-variables that absorbs the per-Оұ slash-adjoint shift on the
DS double-coset side.  Combined with `Gamma_p_Оұ_conjBy_spec` (the
matrix-coset bijection `О“_p(Оұ) вү… Оұ' В· О“_p(Оұ) В· Оұ'вҒ»В№` at the SL/GLвӮӮ(в„қ)
level) and `conjGL_map_eq_conjAct_inv_smul_inter` (the GL-level
identity bridging `conjGL` and `ConjAct.toConjAct _ вҖў _`), the
adapter's conjugate-subgroup output identifies with the matrix-coset
image of `Оұ В· О“_p(Оұ) В· ОұвҒ»В№`. -/
theorem isFundamentalDomain_GLPos_smul_conjAct
    (Оұ' : GL(2, в„қ)вҒә) {HвӮҒ : Subgroup (GL(2, в„қ)вҒә)} {s : Set в„Қ}
    (hs : MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain (HвӮҒ : Subgroup (GL(2, в„қ)вҒә)) s Ој_hyp) :
    MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain
      ((ConjAct.toConjAct Оұ' вҖў HвӮҒ : Subgroup (GL(2, в„қ)вҒә)))
      (Оұ' вҖў s) Ој_hyp :=
  MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain.smul_of_eq_conjAct hs rfl

open CongruenceSubgroup Pointwise ConjAct UpperHalfPlane MeasureTheory in
/-- **T090 / T106 FD-shift adapter for `О“_p(Оұ)` (GL(2, в„қ)вҒә lift,
conditional input hypothesis)**.

Specialization of `isFundamentalDomain_GLPos_smul_conjAct` at
`HвӮҒ := (Gamma_p_Оұ Оұ).map ModularGroup.coeHom`.  From a fundamental
domain `s` for the `GL(2, в„қ)вҒә`-lift of `О“_p(Оұ)`, derive a fundamental
domain for the Оұ'-translate `Оұ' вҖў s` and the conjugate subgroup
`ConjAct.toConjAct Оұ' вҖў ((О“_p(Оұ)).map ModularGroup.coeHom)`.

The conjugate subgroup matches `Оұ В· О“_p(Оұ) В· ОұвҒ»В№` at the matrix-coset
level (modulo the bijection in `Gamma_p_Оұ_conjBy_spec`).

**Conditional input вҖ” kernel obstruction.**  The input hypothesis
`IsFundamentalDomain ((О“_p(Оұ)).map ModularGroup.coeHom) s Ој_hyp` is
**provably FALSE** when `-I вҲҲ О“_p(Оұ)`, equivalently when `-I вҲҲ О“вӮҒ(N)`
i.e. `N вҲҲ {1, 2}` (since `О“_p(Оұ) := conjGL О“вӮҒ(N) Оұ' вҠ“ О“вӮҒ(N)` and `-I`
lies in `О“вӮҒ(N) вҲ© conjGL О“вӮҒ(N) Оұ'` whenever `-I вҲҲ О“вӮҒ(N)`).  The
pairwise `AEDisjoint` field of `IsFundamentalDomain` cannot hold when
the action has nontrivial kernel `{ВұI}` вҖ” distinct group elements
`gвӮҒ = 1` and `gвӮӮ = -I` give `gвӮҒ вҖў s = gвӮӮ вҖў s = s`, so
`AEDisjoint Ој_hyp s s` would force `s` measure-zero.

**Resolution route (open).**  For general `N` the GL(2, в„қ)вҒә-subgroup
input FD is unsupported.  The replacement API is to lift the FD-shift
adapter to the projective ambient `PGL(2, в„қ)вҒә := GL(2, в„қ)вҒә / scalars`,
where the `ВұI` kernel is moded out and `Оұ` retains a well-defined
image.  This adapter remains usable as-is for `N вүҘ 3` (where `-I вҲү О“вӮҒ(N)`
makes the action faithful and the input FD provable from
`isFundamentalDomain_Gamma1_PSL` plus a `О“вӮҒ(N).map coeHom вүғ imageGamma1_PSL N`
isomorphism), but downstream consumption in `DSDoubleCosetTileBridge`
should not assume `N вүҘ 3` and is therefore blocked on the projective
route. -/
theorem Gamma_p_Оұ_GLPos_lift_FD_smul_conjAct
    (Оұ : GL (Fin 2) в„ҡ) (Оұ' : GL(2, в„қ)вҒә) {s : Set в„Қ}
    (hs : IsFundamentalDomain
      ((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map
        (ModularGroup.coeHom : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL(2, в„қ)вҒә))
      s Ој_hyp) :
    IsFundamentalDomain
      (ConjAct.toConjAct Оұ' вҖў
        ((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map
          (ModularGroup.coeHom : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL(2, в„қ)вҒә)) :
          Subgroup GL(2, в„қ)вҒә)
      (Оұ' вҖў s) Ој_hyp :=
  isFundamentalDomain_GLPos_smul_conjAct Оұ' hs

open CongruenceSubgroup Pointwise UpperHalfPlane MeasureTheory in
/-- **T090 / T106 finite-index FD decomposition for `О“_p(Оұ) вүӨ О“вӮҒ(N)`
(conditional ambient form)**.

For any group `G_outer` containing both `О“вӮҒ(N)` and `О“_p(Оұ)` via a fixed
group hom `ПҶ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* G_outer`, and for any `О“вӮҒ(N).map ПҶ`-fundamental
domain `D` on в„Қ, the union of `[О“вӮҒ(N) : О“_p(Оұ)]`-many translates indexed
by `О“вӮҒ(N).map ПҶ в§ё ((О“_p(Оұ).map ПҶ).subgroupOf (О“вӮҒ(N).map ПҶ))` is a
fundamental domain for the inner subgroup
`(О“_p(Оұ).map ПҶ).subgroupOf (О“вӮҒ(N).map ПҶ)`.

**Direct specialization** of the generic
`MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain.subgroup_iUnion_out_smul`
(`PeterssonLevelN.lean`:304) at the named subgroup pair `О“_p(Оұ) вүӨ О“вӮҒ(N)`
(lifted via `ПҶ`).  The `Countable` hypothesis on the right-coset space
is `[О“вӮҒ(N) : О“_p(Оұ)]`-finite-index from `Gamma_p_Оұ_finiteIndex_in_Gamma1`
(transferred under `ПҶ` for injective `ПҶ`); supplied as an instance
argument so the caller wires it in at the ambient level.

**Conditional ambient вҖ” kernel obstruction.**  This theorem is itself
unconditional, but its *useful* instantiations require the input
hypothesis `IsFundamentalDomain ((О“вӮҒ(N)).map ПҶ) D Ој_hyp` to actually be
satisfiable for the chosen `(G_outer, ПҶ)`.  The latter depends on the
faithfulness of the `(О“вӮҒ(N)).map ПҶ`-action on в„Қ:

* **PSL ambient** (`G_outer := PSL(2, в„Ө)`, `ПҶ := QuotientGroup.mk' вҹЁВұIвҹ©`):
  the input FD is `isFundamentalDomain_Gamma1_PSL` (existing,
  `PeterssonLevelN.lean`:540).  Always available.  Limitation: cannot
  feed `Gamma_p_Оұ_GLPos_lift_FD_smul_conjAct` because the Hecke matrix
  `Оұ : GL (Fin 2) в„ҡ` does not embed into `PSL(2, в„Ө)` (its determinant
  varies).

* **GL(2, в„қ)вҒә ambient** (`G_outer := GL(2, в„қ)вҒә`,
  `ПҶ := ModularGroup.coeHom`): the input FD `IsFundamentalDomain
  ((О“вӮҒ(N)).map ModularGroup.coeHom) D Ој_hyp` is **provably FALSE** when
  `-I вҲҲ О“вӮҒ(N)`, i.e., when `N вҲҲ {1, 2}` вҖ” the `ВұI` kernel of the
  MГ¶bius action collapses distinct group elements onto the same
  set-translate, breaking the pairwise `AEDisjoint` field of
  `IsFundamentalDomain`.  For `N вүҘ 3` the action is faithful and the
  bridge is in principle provable, but no proof has been landed.

* **PGL(2, в„қ)вҒә / projective ambient** (proposed): use the projective
  quotient `GL(2, в„қ)вҒә / scalars` where the `ВұI` kernel is moded out and
  `Оұ` retains a well-defined image.  This is the natural replacement
  API for general `N`, and is the next bridge step before downstream
  `DSDoubleCosetTileBridge` consumption.

**Use site (DS Prop. 5.5.2(b), conditional).**  Combined with the
FD-shift adapter `Gamma_p_Оұ_GLPos_lift_FD_smul_conjAct` (at the
projective-equivalent ambient), this would provide the per-Оұ
tile-decomposition needed for the `DSDoubleCosetTileBridge` proof:
starting from a О“вӮҒ(N)-FD `D`, decompose into a О“_p(Оұ)-FD via the
finite-index coset-tile union, then Оұ-shift the result to obtain the
`Оұ В· О“_p(Оұ) В· ОұвҒ»В№`-FD whose Petersson integral hosts the per-Оұ
slash-adjoint shift.  The wiring is blocked on landing the projective
ambient (or restricting to `N вүҘ 3` if the project caller commits to
that hypothesis). -/
theorem Gamma_p_Оұ_FD_finite_index_decomp
    {G_outer : Type*} [Group G_outer] [MulAction G_outer в„Қ]
    [MeasurableConstSMul G_outer в„Қ] [SMulInvariantMeasure G_outer в„Қ Ој_hyp]
    (Оұ : GL (Fin 2) в„ҡ) (ПҶ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* G_outer) {D : Set в„Қ}
    (hD : IsFundamentalDomain ((Gamma1 N).map ПҶ) D Ој_hyp)
    [Countable
      (((Gamma1 N).map ПҶ) в§ё
        (((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map ПҶ).subgroupOf ((Gamma1 N).map ПҶ)))] :
    IsFundamentalDomain
      (((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map ПҶ).subgroupOf ((Gamma1 N).map ПҶ))
      (вӢғ q : ((Gamma1 N).map ПҶ) в§ё
              (((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map ПҶ).subgroupOf ((Gamma1 N).map ПҶ)),
        ((q.out : ((Gamma1 N).map ПҶ)) : G_outer)вҒ»В№ вҖў D)
      Ој_hyp :=
  hD.subgroup_iUnion_out_smul _

/-! ### Phase D: PSL(2, в„қ) ambient instantiations of the FD-shift adapters

We re-instantiate the generic GL(2, в„қ)вҒә adapters from above at the
projective real ambient `PSL(2, в„қ)`, using the Phase AвҖ“C foundation
(`MulAction PSL(2, в„қ) в„Қ`, `instSMulInvMeasure_PSL_R`, `SL2Z_to_PSL2R`,
`isFundamentalDomain_Gamma1_PSL_R`, `GLPos_to_PSL_R_term`).  Unlike the
`GL(2, в„қ)вҒә`-subgroup version, the projective ambient hosts a satisfiable
input FD for *any* `[NeZero N]` (no `ВұI`-kernel obstruction), and the
`Оұ'`-shift uses the term-level projective representative
`GLPos_to_PSL_R_term Оұ' : PSL(2, в„қ)`. -/

open CongruenceSubgroup Pointwise ConjAct UpperHalfPlane MeasureTheory in
/-- **Phase D step 2 вҖ” generic projective FD-shift adapter at PSL(2, в„қ)**.

From a fundamental domain `s` for an arbitrary subgroup `HвӮҒ вүӨ PSL(2, в„қ)`
acting on в„Қ via the projective MГ¶bius action (with `Ој_hyp`-invariance from
`instSMulInvMeasure_PSL_R` in `PSL2Action.lean`), derive a fundamental
domain for the Оұ-translate `Оұ вҖў s` and the Оұ-conjugate subgroup
`ConjAct.toConjAct Оұ вҖў HвӮҒ`.

Direct application of Tertiary's
`MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain.smul_of_eq_conjAct`
(`PeterssonLevelN.lean`:428), instantiated at `G_outer := PSL(2, в„қ)`. -/
theorem isFundamentalDomain_PSL_R_smul_conjAct
    (Оұ : PSL(2, в„қ)) {HвӮҒ : Subgroup (PSL(2, в„қ))} {s : Set в„Қ}
    (hs : MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain (HвӮҒ : Subgroup (PSL(2, в„қ))) s Ој_hyp) :
    MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain
      ((ConjAct.toConjAct Оұ вҖў HвӮҒ : Subgroup (PSL(2, в„қ))))
      (Оұ вҖў s) Ој_hyp :=
  MeasureTheory.IsFundamentalDomain.smul_of_eq_conjAct hs rfl

open CongruenceSubgroup in
/-- **Phase E1 вҖ” finite-index instance for the projective image of `О“_p(Оұ)`
inside the projective image of `О“вӮҒ(N)`.**

The subgroup `(О“_p(Оұ)).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R` has finite index in
`(О“вӮҒ(N)).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R`, lifting the integer-side finite-index witness
`Gamma_p_Оұ_finiteIndex` along the (non-injective) hom `SL2Z_to_PSL2R`.

**Key lemma**: `Subgroup.relIndex_map_map` rewrites
`((map f H).subgroupOf (map f K)).index = (map f H).relIndex (map f K)
  = (H вҠ” f.ker).relIndex (K вҠ” f.ker)`.
Since `О“_p(Оұ)` already has finite index in `SL(2, в„Ө)` (`Gamma_p_Оұ_finiteIndex`),
so does the larger group `О“_p(Оұ) вҠ” ker SL2Z_to_PSL2R`
(`Subgroup.finiteIndex_of_le`), and consequently its `subgroupOf` has finite
index (`Subgroup.instFiniteIndex_subgroupOf`).

**Use site**: provides the `[Countable вҖҰ]` instance hypothesis required by
`Gamma_p_Оұ_PSL_R_FD_finite_index_decomp` automatically, removing the need
for downstream callers to thread that instance manually. -/
instance Gamma_p_Оұ_image_PSL_R_finiteIndex_in_Gamma1_image
    (Оұ : GL (Fin 2) в„ҡ) :
    (((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R).subgroupOf
      ((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R)).FiniteIndex := by
  haveI : (Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).FiniteIndex := Gamma_p_Оұ_finiteIndex Оұ
  haveI : (Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ вҠ” SL2Z_to_PSL2R.ker).FiniteIndex :=
    Subgroup.finiteIndex_of_le le_sup_left
  refine вҹЁ?_вҹ©
  show ((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R).relIndex
        ((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R) вү  0
  rw [Subgroup.relIndex_map_map]
  exact (Subgroup.instFiniteIndex_subgroupOf
    (Gamma1 N вҠ” SL2Z_to_PSL2R.ker)
    (H := Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ вҠ” SL2Z_to_PSL2R.ker)).index_ne_zero

open CongruenceSubgroup in
/-- **Phase E1 (companion) вҖ” `Fintype` of the right-coset space.**

The `Fintype` instance on the quotient `((О“вӮҒ(N)).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R) в§ё
(((О“_p(Оұ)).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R).subgroupOf ((О“вӮҒ(N)).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R))`
follows directly from `Gamma_p_Оұ_image_PSL_R_finiteIndex_in_Gamma1_image`
via `Subgroup.fintypeQuotientOfFiniteIndex`.  Noncomputable.

The downstream `[Countable вҖҰ]` instance argument of
`Gamma_p_Оұ_PSL_R_FD_finite_index_decomp` is satisfied via the standard
`[Fintype] вҶ’ [Finite] вҶ’ [Countable]` chain. -/
noncomputable instance Gamma_p_Оұ_image_PSL_R_quotient_fintype
    (Оұ : GL (Fin 2) в„ҡ) :
    Fintype
      (((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R) в§ё
        (((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R).subgroupOf
          ((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R))) :=
  Subgroup.fintypeQuotientOfFiniteIndex

open CongruenceSubgroup Pointwise UpperHalfPlane MeasureTheory in
/-- **Phase D step 3 вҖ” finite-index FD decomposition for `О“_p(Оұ) вүӨ О“вӮҒ(N)`
at the PSL(2, в„қ) ambient.**

Specialization of the generic `Gamma_p_Оұ_FD_finite_index_decomp` at
`(G_outer, ПҶ) := (PSL(2, в„қ), SL2Z_to_PSL2R)` and the input FD
`isFundamentalDomain_Gamma1_PSL_R` (`PeterssonLevelN.lean`), bridged via
`map_SL2Z_to_PSL2R_eq_imageGamma1_PSL_R` (`PeterssonLevelN.lean`).

The `Countable` hypothesis on the right-coset space is supplied as an
instance argument; downstream callers derive it automatically from
`Gamma_p_Оұ_image_PSL_R_quotient_countable` (Phase E1, in scope above). -/
theorem Gamma_p_Оұ_PSL_R_FD_finite_index_decomp
    (Оұ : GL (Fin 2) в„ҡ)
    [Countable
      (((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R) в§ё
        (((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R).subgroupOf
          ((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R)))] :
    IsFundamentalDomain
      (((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R).subgroupOf
        ((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R))
      (вӢғ q : ((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R) в§ё
              (((Gamma_p_Оұ (N := N) Оұ).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R).subgroupOf
                ((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R)),
        ((q.out : ((Gamma1 N).map SL2Z_to_PSL2R)) : PSL(2, в„қ))вҒ»В№ вҖў
          Gamma1_fundDomain_PSL N)
      Ој_hyp := by
  apply Gamma_p_Оұ_FD_finite_index_decomp Оұ SL2Z_to_PSL2R
  rw [map_SL2Z_to_PSL2R_eq_imageGamma1_PSL_R]
  exact isFundamentalDomain_Gamma1_PSL_R

