/-- **T024 LHS per-Оұ HeckeFD aggregate (real bridge theorem).**

DS 5.5.2(b) LHS reduction: aggregates `petN(T_p f, g)` into a single
Petersson integral over the **per-Оұ aggregate Hecke fundamental domain**
`Оұ вҖў О“вӮҒ_FD := вӢғ_q (glMap Оұ * mapGL qвҒ»В№) вҖў fd` for `Оұ вҲҲ {M_вҲһ} вҲӘ {T_p_upper(b)
: b < p}`, with **uniform slot-2 = `g вҲЈ T_p_lower`**:

```
petN (T_p f) g =
  peterssonInner (M_вҲһ вҖў О“вӮҒ_FD) f (g вҲЈ T_p_lower) +
  вҲ‘_b peterssonInner (T_p_upper(b) вҖў О“вӮҒ_FD) f (g вҲЈ T_p_lower)
```

**Real theorem with explicit finite-family/tile assumptions** (per manager
directive). Composes:

* `petN_heckeT_p_eq_per_q_T_p_lower_form` (per-q distributed form);
* `Finset.sum_add_distrib` (sum over `q` distributes over the M_вҲһ-tile +
  upper-union summand pair);
* `peterssonInner_iUnion_finite_aedisjoint.symm` (q-aggregation for each
  Оұ: turns `вҲ‘_q peterssonInner_Оұ_q_tile` into a single
  `peterssonInner` over the q-union);
* `peterssonInner_biUnion_finset_ae` (per-q b-expansion: turns the
  upper-`b` union-tile `peterssonInner` into `вҲ‘_b peterssonInner b-tile`);
* `Finset.sum_comm` (swap inner `q` and `b` sums to enable per-`b`
  q-aggregation).

**Hypotheses (explicit per-Оұ tile family AE-disjointness, null-measurability,
integrability).** -/
private theorem petN_heckeT_p_eq_per_alpha_HeckeFD_form
    (p : в„•) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
