open UpperHalfPlane ModularGroup MeasureTheory in
/-- **T024 per-q tile-sum match from per-tile matches.**

Reduces the per-q tile-sum match obligation expected by
`petN_heckeT_p_adjoint_standard_form_of_per_q_tile_match` to **per-tile**
identifications: one for the `M_вҲһ` tile (index `0` in `Fin (p+1)`) and one
per `T_p_upper(b)` tile (index `b.succ` for `b : Fin p`).  Each per-tile
hypothesis is the **scalar identity** equating one bundle tile's Petersson
inner product to its corresponding M_вҲһ / T_p_upper-branch in the per-`q`
distributed RHS form produced by `petN_diamond_heckeT_p_symm_RHS_sum_distributed`.

This is the **exact DS 5.5.2(b) per-q tile identity** required by the consumer
chain.  The classical geometric content of DS 5.5.2(b) вҖ” the per-tile slash-
adjoint / fundamental-domain shift identification вҖ” appears here as explicit
hypotheses, narrower than the global `h_tile_match` (and narrower than the
per-`q` hypothesis of `_of_per_q_tile_match`): each per-tile hypothesis is a
scalar Petersson equality, not an aggregate.

**Proof.**  `Fin.sum_univ_succ` splits the `Fin (p+1)` sum into its zero
component (the `M_вҲһ` tile) and a `Fin p` sum over the successors (the
`T_p_upper(b)` tiles).  Per-tile hypotheses discharge each piece, and
`Fin.sum_univ_eq_sum_range` converts the `Fin p` sum to the canonical
`Finset.range p` form.

**Mathematical reference.**  DiamondвҖ“Shurman, *A First Course in Modular
Forms*, Prop. 5.5.2(b); Miyake В§4.5. -/
private theorem peterssonInner_M_infty_T_p_upper_tile_sum_matches_per_q_distribute
    (p : в„•) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (q : SL(2, в„Ө) в§ё Gamma1 N)
    (f g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL в„қ)) k)
    (g_const : UpperHalfPlane вҶ’ в„Ӯ)
    (tile : Fin (p + 1) вҶ’ Set UpperHalfPlane)
    (h_tile_zero_match :
      peterssonInner k (tile 0) вҮ‘f g_const =
      peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
          ((вҮ‘f вҲЈ[k] ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
              (((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№) :
              GL (Fin 2) в„қ)) вҲЈ[k]
            ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
              (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№))
          (вҮ‘g вҲЈ[k]
            ((glMap (M_infty N p hp.pos hpN) : GL (Fin 2) в„қ) *
              ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
                (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№ : GL (Fin 2) в„қ))))
    (h_tile_succ_match : вҲҖ b : Fin p,
      peterssonInner k (tile b.succ) вҮ‘f g_const =
      peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
            ((вҮ‘f вҲЈ[k] ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
                (((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№) :
                GL (Fin 2) в„қ)) вҲЈ[k]
              ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
                (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№))
            (вҮ‘g вҲЈ[k]
              ((glMap (T_p_upper p hp.pos b.val) : GL (Fin 2) в„қ) *
                ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
                  (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№ : GL (Fin 2) в„қ)))) :
    вҲ‘ i : Fin (p + 1), peterssonInner k (tile i) вҮ‘f g_const =
      peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
          ((вҮ‘f вҲЈ[k] ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
              (((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№) :
              GL (Fin 2) в„қ)) вҲЈ[k]
            ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
              (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№))
          (вҮ‘g вҲЈ[k]
            ((glMap (M_infty N p hp.pos hpN) : GL (Fin 2) в„қ) *
              ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
                (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№ : GL (Fin 2) в„қ))) +
        вҲ‘ b вҲҲ Finset.range p,
          peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
            ((вҮ‘f вҲЈ[k] ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
                (((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№) :
                GL (Fin 2) в„қ)) вҲЈ[k]
              ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
                (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№))
            (вҮ‘g вҲЈ[k]
              ((glMap (T_p_upper p hp.pos b) : GL (Fin 2) в„қ) *
                ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
                  (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№ : GL (Fin 2) в„қ))) := by
  rw [Fin.sum_univ_succ, h_tile_zero_match]
  congr 1
  rw [show (вҲ‘ b : Fin p, peterssonInner k (tile b.succ) вҮ‘f g_const) =
      вҲ‘ b : Fin p,
        peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
          ((вҮ‘f вҲЈ[k] ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
              (((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№) :
              GL (Fin 2) в„қ)) вҲЈ[k]
            ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
              (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№))
          (вҮ‘g вҲЈ[k]
            ((glMap (T_p_upper p hp.pos b.val) : GL (Fin 2) в„қ) *
              ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
                (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№ : GL (Fin 2) в„қ)))
    from Finset.sum_congr rfl fun b _ => h_tile_succ_match b]
  exact Fin.sum_univ_eq_sum_range
    (fun n : в„• => peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd
      ((вҮ‘f вҲЈ[k] ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
          (((adjointGamma0Rep p N hpN : Gamma0 N) : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№) :
          GL (Fin 2) в„қ)) вҲЈ[k]
        ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
          (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№))
      (вҮ‘g вҲЈ[k]
        ((glMap (T_p_upper p hp.pos n) : GL (Fin 2) в„қ) *
          ((mapGL в„қ : SL(2, в„Ө) вҶ’* GL (Fin 2) в„қ)
            (q.out : SL(2, в„Ө))вҒ»В№ : GL (Fin 2) в„қ)))) p

open UpperHalfPlane ModularGroup MeasureTheory in
/-- **T024 per-tile match reduction via `peterssonInner_slash_adjoint`.**

Reduces a per-tile Petersson scalar identity of the form expected at
`peterssonInner_M_infty_T_p_upper_tile_sum_matches_per_q_distribute`'s
per-tile hypotheses to **three atomic inputs**:

* `h_tile_eq`: tile AE-equals `ОІ вҖў fd` for some positive-det `ОІ : GLвӮӮ(в„қ)`
  (the **tile shape** вҖ” geometric content from the bundle's
  `IsFundamentalDomain`-shifted construction);
* `h_slash_slot1`: matrix algebra on slot-1 (`f вҲЈ ОІ = (f вҲЈ Оұ) вҲЈ Оі` for the
  desired slot-1 form);
* `h_slash_slot2`: matrix algebra on slot-2
  (`g_const вҲЈ (peterssonAdj ОІ)вҒ»В№ = ПҲ_g`).

This is a **strictly narrower** factoring of `h_tile_zero_match` /
`h_tile_succ_match` from the previous reduction theorem: the per-tile
identification is replaced by tile-shape + per-slot matrix-algebra inputs.
The slash-adjoint identity (mathlib-style content) is discharged inline.

**Proof.** The tile-shape AE-equality rewrites the integration domain to
`ОІ вҖў fd`. The standard `g_const = (g_const вҲЈ (peterssonAdj ОІ)вҒ»В№) вҲЈ peterssonAdj ОІ`
decomposition + `peterssonInner_slash_adjoint` (backward) then converts
`peterssonInner k (ОІ вҖў fd) f g_const` to
`peterssonInner k fd (f вҲЈ ОІ) (g_const вҲЈ (peterssonAdj ОІ)вҒ»В№)`. The two matrix-
algebra hypotheses discharge the slot identifications.

**Mathematical reference.** DiamondвҖ“Shurman, *A First Course in Modular
Forms*, Prop. 5.5.2(b); Miyake В§4.5. -/
private theorem peterssonInner_per_tile_match_via_slash_adjoint
    (ОІ : GL (Fin 2) в„қ) (hОІ : 0 < ОІ.det.val)
    {tile_target : Set UpperHalfPlane}
    (F G : UpperHalfPlane вҶ’ в„Ӯ)
    (slot1_target slot2_target : UpperHalfPlane вҶ’ в„Ӯ)
    (h_tile_eq : tile_target =бөҗ[Ој_hyp] ОІ вҖў ModularGroup.fd)
    (h_slash_slot1 : F вҲЈ[k] ОІ = slot1_target)
    (h_slash_slot2 : G вҲЈ[k] (peterssonAdj ОІ)вҒ»В№ = slot2_target) :
    peterssonInner k tile_target F G =
      peterssonInner k ModularGroup.fd slot1_target slot2_target := by
  have h_tile_inner :
      peterssonInner k tile_target F G =
        peterssonInner k (ОІ вҖў ModularGroup.fd) F G := by
    simp only [peterssonInner]
    exact setIntegral_congr_set h_tile_eq
  rw [h_tile_inner]
  have h_G_decomp : G = (G вҲЈ[k] (peterssonAdj ОІ)вҒ»В№) вҲЈ[k] peterssonAdj ОІ := by
    rw [вҶҗ SlashAction.slash_mul, inv_mul_cancel, SlashAction.slash_one]
  conv_lhs => rw [h_G_decomp]
  rw [вҶҗ peterssonInner_slash_adjoint ModularGroup.fd ОІ hОІ F
        (G вҲЈ[k] (peterssonAdj ОІ)вҒ»В№), h_slash_slot1, h_slash_slot2]

