hypothesis `h_tile_eq` covering all `p + 1` tiles (since by the closed-branch
construction all tiles share the same shift `ОІ = mapGL ОівӮҖвҒ»В№ * mapGL q.outвҒ»В№`).

The LHS uses **per-tile g_const** values produced by the closed branches:
`g вҲЈ (M_вҲһ * mapGL ОівӮҖ)` for tile `0` and `g вҲЈ (T_p_upper(b) * mapGL ОівӮҖ)` for
tile `b.succ`. The RHS is the canonical per-q distributed form.

This is the **SMO-critical theorem-level deliverable** completing the per-q
DS adjoint chain: only the tile-shape AE equality remains as the genuine
geometric atomic input from the bundle's M_вҲһ/T_p_upper coset construction.

**Mathematical reference.**  DiamondвҖ“Shurman, *A First Course in Modular
Forms*, Prop. 5.5.2(b); Miyake В§4.5. -/
private theorem peterssonInner_per_q_distributed_form_via_closed_branches
    (p : в„•) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hpN : Nat.Coprime p N)
    (q : SL(2, в„Ө) в§ё Gamma1 N)
    (g : CuspForm ((Gamma1 N).map (mapGL в„қ)) k)
    (F : UpperHalfPlane вҶ’ в„Ӯ)
    (tile : Fin (p + 1) вҶ’ Set UpperHalfPlane)
