/-- **T090 reusable reduction**: symmetric Hecke adjoint from unsymmetric.

Given the unsymmetric T_p adjoint identity in its canonical DiamondвҖ“Shurman
form `petN(T_p f, g) = petN(f, вҹЁpвҹ©вҒ»В№(T_p g))`, derive the symmetric form
